This paper discusses the use of ontologies and symbolic reasoning in human-robot interaction scenarios, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of scripting paradigms and the optimization of performance, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of formal axioms and knowledge representation, which could be related to programming languages (cs.PL).
